<p><b>Translated to Welsh</b></p>
<p>
    Section 12(1)(b) of the Transport Act 1985 (as amended) requires all applicants for special restricted public
    service vehicle operators licences to state in their application that they propose to provide a registered local bus
    service. You are therefore making the following declaration when submitting this application
</p>
<p>
    <strong>
        I confirm that I propose to use one or more licensed taxis or private hire vehicles to provide a local service
    </strong>
</p>
<p><strong>I declare that:</strong></p>
<ul class="bullet">
    <li>
        The statements made in this application are true. I understand that it is an offence to make a false declaration
    </li>
    <li>The applicant is the holder of the taxi or private hire vehicle licence(s) listed in this application.</li>
    <li>
        Every vehicle used under the special restricted PSV operator’s licence shall be one for which the applicant
        holds a taxi or private hire vehicle licence.
    </li>
    <li>
        No vehicle shall be used under the special restricted PSV operator’s licence otherwise than for the purpose of
        providing a local service with one or more stopping places within the area which granted the relevant licence
        for that vehicle.
    </li>
</ul>
